column10:
At first it started with just basic objects.
A lighter pinkish ball moving from one side of the screen to another; 
Double beam of lights, this time light blue, moving like a lighthouse beam would, except there's two, both stemming from a single point in the middle;
 4 beams, top, bottom, left, and right, respectively, looked like a cross for a bit, but then morphed where the perspective got clearer. It seemed as if you're looking up from the inside of a box. Then it extended, as if you're on the bottom looking up from a structurally unsound (was not a straight line) elevator shaft.

The basic shapes were the most common. I.e. the elevator scene went away, and it was back to that single ball moving back and forth. This time it was without a solid border though: less like the game pong, more like watching the divider in the street pass you, if you were to be looking down at it while driving or something. 

Had a flash of a bridge; of a birds eye view of a city; i want to say a beach? but was too short to hold on.
